diff:1668383775:1668226665:=49,77c49%0a%3c #foxbegin 221113-235615-290850#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Null Copula in Headlinese %0a%3c -> - johnternullo%0a%3c -> [-13.11.2022 - 15:56-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221113-235615-290850 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c Headlinese is a term used for the English used in headlines such as those found in newspapers.%0a%3c %0a%3c Headlinese differs from most varieties of English due to being influenced by the need to condense information into shorter titles and to grab the attention of readers.%0a%3c %0a%3c As a result, headlines often appear without forms of the verb "to be" where they would be present in other dialects of English.%0a%3c %0a%3c The indefinite and definite articles are also frequently removed, and the infinitive form of a verb can be used to represent the future tense.%0a%3c %0a%3c Example:%0a%3c "Tribe officials acquitted in North Dakota pipeline protests"%0a%3c As opposed to "Tribe officials are acquitted..." in other varieties of English%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c https://ygdp.yale.edu/phenomena/null-copula%0a%3c http://www.isabelperez.com/module4_tesis/headlines.htm%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221113-235615-290850#%0a---%0a> %0a
