diff:1668226665:1668226665:=1,84d0%0a%3c (:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0a%3c Status: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!{$:Category}]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Null Copula%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: ssbisht%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Null Copula in African American English%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Null copula refers to the absence of a form of the verb “be” in English sentences. Null copula is commonly seen in African American English and other varieties of English that have had high contact with other languages. This is because many other languages often have null copulas in the present tense. For example, in the sentence “They are happy”, a version displaying null copula would be “They happy”. Null copula is mainly seen in the present tense, that is, “is” and “are”. There are also some exceptions where null copula can’t occur, for instance clause-final positions for the form of “be”. Additionally, there is an interesting relationship between occurrences of null copula in AAE and Standardized American English: deletion of “is” or “are” in AAE occurs if and only if Standardized American English could contract the verb. Because of this relationship with contraction, some argue that null copula is a result of phonological processes.%0a%3c %0a%3c I chose to talk about this grammatical construction because I have seen something similar in Latin, which I learned for several years. In Latin, the removal of forms of “to be” is a perfectly valid construction and is even often used for poetic purposes. The fact that people are discriminated against for using a grammatical construction that is often seen in languages across the world, but not in Standardized American English, seems very unfair to me because there is no “best” or “most correct” variety of a language.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: E:)%0a%3c (:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversityOfEnglish:)%0a%3c (:Title: Null Copula:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
